<solution>
    <p>[+++++++++++++++]</p>
    <ol>
      <li>Sample response: Andre’s reasoning makes sense because that is showing <m>\frac{1}{2}</m> of the length just like we did on our fraction strips. Clare’s reasoning makes sense because you can label the point on the number line just like we did with other numbers.</li>
      <li>Students will have 5 number lines. One of each folded into halves, thirds, fourths, sixths, and eighths with the corresponding unit fraction labeled on each one.</li>
    </ol>
  </solution>


